SmartAttend BRD
1. Executive Summary

SmartAttend is a proposed digital attendance management system designed to replace manual attendance registers in universities. The system uses NFC-enabled student cards to automatically record attendance, improving accuracy, efficiency, and data reliability.

2. Business Problem

Current attendance systems rely on manual registers, which lead to:

Proxy attendance (students signing for others)
Lost or damaged records
Time-consuming lecture processes
Lack of real-time reporting
Difficulty identifying at-risk students
3. Business Objectives
Digitize attendance tracking
Improve accuracy and reliability of attendance data
Reduce administrative workload
Provide real-time reporting for lecturers and administrators
4. Scope

In Scope:

Student attendance tracking
Lecturer dashboards
Admin management system
Reporting system

Out of Scope:

Payroll systems
Full academic grading systems
5. Stakeholders
Students: record attendance
Lecturers: view and manage class attendance
Administrators: manage system users and data
IT Support: maintain system infrastructure
6. Assumptions
Students have NFC-enabled ID cards
Lecturers use digital devices in classrooms
Internet connectivity is available on campus
7. Constraints
Limited budget for hardware
Dependence on NFC technology
System must be simple for non-technical users
8. Success Criteria
95% reduction in manual attendance usage
Real-time attendance visibility
Reduction in proxy attendance incidents
